<zyQSetMultipleChoice caption="Data wrangling vs. ETL" id="6beefd5a-9993-4193-9d9a-87fad770af95">

<zyQ>
<zyQText>Which process structures, cleans, and enriches data?</zyQText>
<zyQChoice>
<zyQAns>Data wrangling only</zyQAns>
<zyQExpl>The "T" in ETL stands for transform. Transforming data includes structuring, cleaning, and enriching.</zyQExpl>
</zyQChoice>
<zyQChoice>
<zyQAns>ETL only</zyQAns>
<zyQExpl>Structuring, cleaning, and enriching data are steps 2-4 of data wrangling.</zyQExpl>
</zyQChoice>
<zyQChoice correct="true">
<zyQAns>Both data wrangling and ETL</zyQAns>
<zyQExpl>Structuring, cleaning, and enriching data are steps 2-4 of data wrangling. The "T" in ETL stands for transform. Transforming data includes structuring, cleaning, and enriching.</zyQExpl>
</zyQChoice>
</zyQ>

<zyQ>
<zyQText>Which process periodically extracts data from transactional database systems?</zyQText>
<zyQChoice>
<zyQAns>Data wrangling only</zyQAns>
<zyQExpl>Data wrangling usually entails manual transformation of a static dataset.</zyQExpl>
</zyQChoice>
<zyQChoice correct="true">
<zyQAns>ETL only</zyQAns>
<zyQExpl>ETL is an automated process that periodically extracts data from database systems, then automatically transforms and loads the data to an analytic database.</zyQExpl>
</zyQChoice>
<zyQChoice>
<zyQAns>Both data wrangling and ETL</zyQAns>
<zyQExpl>One of the two processes is usually manual and operates on a static dataset.</zyQExpl>
</zyQChoice>
</zyQ>

<zyQ>
<zyQText>Which ETL tool vendors do not offer database system products? </zyQText>
<zyQChoice correct="true">
<zyQAns>Informatica and Talend</zyQAns>
<zyQExpl>Unlike other vendors listed in the table above, Informatica and Talend offer ETL tools only, not database systems.</zyQExpl>
</zyQChoice>
<zyQChoice>
<zyQAns>IBM and Microsoft</zyQAns>
<zyQExpl>IBM offers DB2 and other database systems. Microsoft offers SQL Server as a stand-alone and cloud product. </zyQExpl>
</zyQChoice>
<zyQChoice>
<zyQAns>Oracle and SAP</zyQAns>
<zyQExpl>Oracle is best known for the Oracle Database product. Although SAP is best know for applications software, SAP also offers the HANA database system.</zyQExpl>
</zyQChoice>
</zyQ>

</zyQSetMultipleChoice>



