<zyQSetMultipleChoice caption="Data wrangling with Python and pandas" id="731c4dc2-b94b-4c16-ac53-8806fec30548">

<zyQ>
<zyQText>Which <zyICode>pandas</zyICode> method imports a dataframe from a CSV file?</zyQText>
<zyQChoice correct="true">
<zyQAns><zyICode>read_csv()</zyICode></zyQAns>
<zyQExpl>A CSV file contains comma-separated values: each feature is separated by a comma. CSV files should be imported in <zyICode>pandas</zyICode> using <zyICode>read_csv()</zyICode>.</zyQExpl>
</zyQChoice>
<zyQChoice>
<zyQAns><zyICode>read_excel()</zyICode></zyQAns>
<zyQExpl>A CSV file contains comma-separated values: each feature is separated by a comma. Excel files contain metadata about the formatting of the Excel worksheet. Using <zyICode>read_excel()</zyICode> with a CSV file will result in an error, since CSV is not the expected file format.</zyQExpl>
</zyQChoice>
<zyQChoice>
<zyQAns><zyICode>read_sql_table()</zyICode></zyQAns>
<zyQExpl>A CSV file contains comma-separated values: each feature is separated by a comma. SQL is used to manipulate relational databases, which often connect multiple data tables together. Using <zyICode>read_sql_table()</zyICode> with a CSV file will result in an error, since CSV is not the expected file format.</zyQExpl>
</zyQChoice>
</zyQ>

<zyQ>
<zyQText>Which <zyICode>pandas</zyICode> method returns information about a dataframe?</zyQText>
<zyQChoice>
<zyQAns><zyICode>dataframe.at[]</zyICode></zyQAns>
<zyQExpl><zyICode>dataframe.at[]</zyICode> returns the value stored at a particular row/column combination in a dataframe. Another pandas method provides information about the entire dataframe vs. a single value.</zyQExpl>
</zyQChoice>
<zyQChoice correct="true">
<zyQAns><zyICode>dataframe.info()</zyICode></zyQAns>
<zyQExpl><zyICode>dataframe.info()</zyICode> returns the column names and indices, feature types, and number of non-null values in a dataframe.</zyQExpl>
</zyQChoice>
<zyQChoice>
<zyQAns><zyICode>dataframe.loc[]</zyICode></zyQAns>
<zyQExpl><zyICode>dataframe.loc[]</zyICode> returns the values stored at a over a range of rows and columns in a dataframe. Another <zyICode>pandas</zyICode> method provides information about the entire dataframe vs. a small subset.</zyQExpl>
</zyQChoice>
</zyQ>

</zyQSetMultipleChoice>


