<zyHTML id="57a5a4a7-fa55-b15b-e956-dec32c3a3972">
<p>
<zyDefn>_dplyr_ is an R package that supports data wrangling.</zyDefn> <zyICode>dplyr</zyICode> is designed for data manipulation on tidy dataframes. <zyDefn>_Tidy data_ is formatted such that each row contains a single instance and each column contains a single feature.</zyDefn> Each column in a dataframe has a data type, such as character or numeric.</p>
</zyHTML>

<zyAside type="elaboration" name="The tidyverse" id="98ee8cbe-0e91-ab24-5fb2-0f24edc48502"> 
<zyICode>dplyr</zyICode> is part of the <zyICode>tidyverse</zyICode> family of packages. <zyDefn>The _tidyverse_ is a set of R packages for data wrangling, data visualization, and modeling with a common structure and syntax.</zyDefn> <zyICode>tidyverse</zyICode>-style packages prioritize readability over conciseness, and use a different syntax than base R.
</zyAside>


