<zyHTML id="592eae48-5d7a-8424-bbdb-0e8f8007163b">
<p><zyICode>dplyr</zyICode> contains six primary functions for data wrangling. These six functions are often called data wrangling verbs, since each function describes a specific action. Multiple data wrangling verbs can be linked using the pipe operator, <zyICode>|></zyICode>, to perform more complex operations. For additional details on <zyICode>dplyr</zyICode> data wrangling functions, see the <zyLink link="https://dplyr.tidyverse.org/">dplyr documentation</zyLink>.</p>
<p>An additional <zyICode>dplyr</zyICode> function, <zyICode>glimpse()</zyICode> can be used to inspect a dataframe. <zyICode>tidyverse</zyICode> functions usually accept both American English and British English spellings. Ex: "summarize" = "summarise" and "color" = "colour".</p>
</zyHTML>

<zyTable id="e06933a8-c4a8-f7ab-f8f7-94039249339d" caption="Data wrangling functions in dplyr">
<table>
<tr>
<th>Function</th>
<th>Description</th>
</tr>

<tr>
<td><zyICode>mutate()</zyICode></td>
<td>Calculate new features using functions of existing features</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td><zyICode>select()</zyICode></td>
<td>Chooses features based on column names</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td><zyICode>filter()</zyICode></td>
<td>Chooses instances based on values of one or more features</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td><zyICode>summarize()</zyICode></td>
<td>Calculate one or more descriptive statistics from features</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td><zyICode>arrange()</zyICode></td>
<td>Sort rows in a dataframe based on one or more features</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td><zyICode>group_by()</zyICode></td>
<td>Group instances into subsets based on values of one or more features (typically combined with another data wrangling verb)</td>
</tr>
</table>
</zyTable>


