<zyQSetMultipleChoice caption="Data wrangling with dplyr" id="0cefa8d1-b756-47e6-908e-052437f756ea">

<zyQ>
<zyQText>Which <zyICode>dplyr</zyICode> function returns information about a dataframe?</zyQText>
<zyQChoice>
<zyQAns><zyICode>filter()</zyICode></zyQAns>
<zyQExpl><zyICode>filter()</zyICode> chooses instances from a dataframe based on values of one or more features. But, <zyICode>filter()</zyICode> does not return information about a dataframe.</zyQExpl>
</zyQChoice>
<zyQChoice correct="true">
<zyQAns><zyICode>glimpse()</zyICode></zyQAns>
<zyQExpl><zyICode>glimpse()</zyICode> shows the feature names, type, and first few values when applied to a dataframe.</zyQExpl>
</zyQChoice>
<zyQChoice>
<zyQAns><zyICode>summarize()</zyICode></zyQAns>
<zyQExpl><zyICode>summarize()</zyICode> calculates user-specified descriptive statistics for features in a dataframe. Another function provides more general information about a dataframe.</zyQExpl>
</zyQChoice>
</zyQ>

<zyQ>
<zyQText>Which <zyICode>dplyr</zyICode> function sorts a dataframe based on values of a feature?</zyQText>
<zyQChoice correct="true">
<zyQAns><zyICode>arrange()</zyICode></zyQAns>
<zyQExpl><zyICode>arrange()</zyICode> sorts a dataframe based on values of a feature. By default, <zyICode>arrange()</zyICode> uses ascending order. Using <zyICode>arrange(desc(Feature))</zyICode> instead sorts in descending order.</zyQExpl>
</zyQChoice>
<zyQChoice>
<zyQAns><zyICode>filter()</zyICode></zyQAns>
<zyQExpl><zyICode>filter()</zyICode> chooses instances from a dataframe based on values of one or more features. But, <zyICode>filter()</zyICode> does not sort a dataframe.</zyQExpl>
</zyQChoice>
<zyQChoice>
<zyQAns><zyICode>group_by()</zyICode></zyQAns>
<zyQExpl><zyICode>group_by()</zyICode> creates subsets of a dataframe based on values of one or more features. But, <zyICode>group_by()</zyICode> does not sort a dataframe.</zyQExpl>
</zyQChoice>
</zyQ>

